    "# \n",
    "With column addition we cant able to add extra values rather than specified before for the existing dataframe,\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "Ex: Here we cant have e, f for four column because its not allowed for extra values for particular column, because if it allow those values for that column then we dont know what are that extra values for remaining columns "
   ]
  },

    "# we can use drop also to delete a row or column but it is not going to reflect in original data\n",

      "2   3   Allen       sub4\n",
      "3   4   Alice       sub6\n",

      "\n",

      "1   2  Brian       sub4\n",
      "2   3   Bran       sub3\n",
      "3   4  Bryce       sub6\n",
      "4   5  Betty       sub5\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "left = pd.DataFrame({\n",
    "   'id':[1,2,3,4,5],\n",
    "   'Name': ['Alex', 'Amy', 'Allen', 'Alice', 'Ayoung'],\n",
    "   'subject_id':['sub1','sub2','sub4','sub6','sub5']})\n",
    "right = pd.DataFrame({\n",
    "\t'id':[1,2,3,4,5],\n",
    "   'Name': ['Billy', 'Brian', 'Bran', 'Bryce', 'Betty'],\n",
    "   'subject_id':['sub2','sub4','sub3','sub6','sub5']})\n",
    "print (left)\n",
    "print ('\\n')\n",
    "print (right)\n"
   ]
